  "binaries": {
    "bin-wr-ednote-0628": {
      "contentType": "text/plain",
      "text": "ED PROVIDER NOTE 6/28/2026\n\nHPI: 68M hx paroxysmal AFib (on apixaban), T2DM, HTN, HLD, chronic LBBB presenting with 1 hour of substernal chest pressure at rest, resolved on arrival. No radiation, no diaphoresis at that time.\n\nED COURSE: hs-troponin 8 -> 9 ng/L (both < 99th percentile URL of 14), delta negative. ECG: LBBB unchanged from 11/2024, no Sgarbossa criteria, cardiology over-read agrees. CXR without acute process. HEART score 5 (moderate) driven by age, risk factors, and history.\n\nDISPO: Discussed with cardiology — discharged with expedited outpatient stress imaging and cardiology follow-up within 2 weeks. Strict return precautions given. Patient verbalized understanding.\n\nNote: patient did not complete the outpatient stress test prior to today's visit per scheduling records."
    },
    "bin-wr-cardnote-0314": {
      "contentType": "text/plain",
      "text": "CARDIOLOGY PROGRESS NOTE 3/14/2026\n\n68M with paroxysmal AFib (CHA2DS2-VASc 4: age, HTN, DM, vascular risk), chronic LBBB since 11/2024, LVEF 45-50% on 12/2025 echo.\n\nASSESSMENT/PLAN:\n1. AFib — rate controlled on metoprolol succinate 50 daily. Continue apixaban 5 BID. No pauses or symptomatic episodes on 14-day monitor (1/2026).\n2. LBBB with mildly reduced EF — likely early nonischemic cardiomyopathy vs tachycardia-mediated; ischemic evaluation NOT yet completed. Stress imaging ordered — patient deferred scheduling.\n3. Counseled on symptoms warranting ED evaluation, including exertional chest pain.\n\nQTc today 452 ms — avoid additive QT-prolonging agents where possible."
    },
